i## Correct Way to Do This		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFor this problem to appear, all three requirements must be met:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i1. **`add paths yes;` option is turned on**, so that secondary routes		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   are sent to other nodes as well. If this option wasn't turned on,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   as soon as the BuyVM node choose the VirMach node as the next hop,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   it won't broadcast its route through Lutoma to the VirMach node.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   Then, the VirMach node will only have the option of sending traffic		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   directly to KSKB.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i2. Route preference algorithm **preferring secondary routes over		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   primary routes from other nodes**. Therefore, if we want to keep		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   `add paths yes;` option on, while designing the iBGP route		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   preference algorithm, we need to guarantee that routes from the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   same node **have their priorities in the same order as that node**,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   so that the primary routes will always be used over secondary		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   routes.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i3. Routes passing Lutoma's network were incorrectly updated with the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   new BGP community, causing the change of route priority orders.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iMy solution to the problem is to no longer recalculate route priority		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifor those received from iBGP. Instead, I will always use the priority		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ivalue calculated by the edge node receiving the route, and passed over		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ialong with the route announcement over iBGP, to guarantee that the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iorder of primary and secondary routes never change.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
